WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.050
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:00:05.050 --> 00:00:10.270
You will work for my organization as "Gido-san."

00:00:10.270 --> 00:00:14.910
I wanted Natsumi-san's status
within the organization.

00:00:14.910 --> 00:00:17.260
You made me ten billion yen.

00:00:17.260 --> 00:00:19.810
Ichika's the one who murdered my wife.

00:00:19.810 --> 00:00:23.700
Promise me you'll arrest her
and will have her fess up her crimes.

00:00:23.700 --> 00:00:27.430
You'd do a fine job replacing Gido.

00:00:27.430 --> 00:00:29.770
I'm not a replacement.

00:00:32.050 --> 00:00:35.090
I am Ayumi Gido.

00:00:35.090 --> 00:00:39.460
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot, Day 35]

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:46.080
A police vehicle is coming through.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:47.950
Please make way.

00:00:47.950 --> 00:00:51.160
Floor it, you're driving like a snail.

00:00:51.160 --> 00:00:53.010
That'd be dangerous, Sir.

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:56.230
And you're eating cream puffs again.

00:01:13.770 --> 00:01:15.390
Coming through.

00:01:18.020 --> 00:01:20.440
Morning.

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:24.870
- Why are you here?
- Natsumi Hayase-san's investigation is on pause.

00:01:24.870 --> 00:01:26.540
- Mr. Gido.
- What's our status?

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:28.580
The victim is Shusuke Igari, age 43.

00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:31.780
Forensics say he died at around 1 a.m.

00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:34.650
He was stabbed in the chest.

00:01:36.250 --> 00:01:41.480
Igari made a living selling drugs
to kids on the street.

00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:43.970
A bonafide scumbag, right?

00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:47.000
- Here.
- Right.

00:01:50.900 --> 00:01:55.700
[Shelter]

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:57.830
It's packed with carrots.

00:01:57.830 --> 00:01:59.690
- Here you go.
- We still have plenty more.

00:01:59.690 --> 00:02:02.800
Smells great in here.

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:08.350
Curry is always a crowdpleaser.

00:02:13.350 --> 00:02:18.150
This happened on the streets of Kabukicho
at around 1 a.m. last night.

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:25.780
Know the kid who killed this guy?

00:02:27.330 --> 00:02:30.450
Masaki Togashi, age 25.

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:33.000
He's one of yours, right?

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:35.820
You're better off telling me the truth.

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:38.970
I'm the only officer who's caught on.

00:02:38.970 --> 00:02:43.520
If the investigation goes on,
they'll find your ties to Fuyuhashi.

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:46.420
Officers would come here in swarms.

00:02:46.420 --> 00:02:50.120
Your kids would lose their home.

00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:56.240
Have the kid turn himself in.

00:02:57.380 --> 00:03:00.270
We'll say it was an act of revenge

00:03:00.270 --> 00:03:03.830
and keep your group out of it.

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:05.320
How's that sound?

00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:11.190
I'll ask Fuyuhashi for his thoughts.

00:03:11.190 --> 00:03:13.060
You'd better hurry.

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:15.750
Thanks for the curry.

00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:19.450
I don't get you.

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:24.690
You're Natsumi-san's husband, aren't you?

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:29.960
It seems like everyone knows nowadays.

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:34.770
Why are you acting like
the man who killed your wife?

00:03:34.770 --> 00:03:37.440
I just don't understand.

00:03:37.440 --> 00:03:41.900
I am backed by our current prime minister.
[29 days ago]

00:03:41.900 --> 00:03:46.360
Find evidence of Goroku
illegally funding his whale,

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:49.940
and we can crush the organization,
Ichika Kogo and all.

00:03:49.940 --> 00:03:54.030
Only then can I guarantee
you and your family's safety.

00:03:55.310 --> 00:03:57.640
How will we find the evidence?

00:03:59.410 --> 00:04:02.090
Elections are on the horizon.

00:04:02.090 --> 00:04:05.580
Goroku will donate in favor of his whale.

00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:08.660
We'll aim for the moment
that transaction is made.

00:04:09.990 --> 00:04:14.540
But you must first build rapport
within the organization.

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:20.240
Are you able to keep up the "bad cop" act?

00:04:23.850 --> 00:04:27.220
I'd do anything to return to my family.

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:31.960
Let me put it this way.

00:04:31.960 --> 00:04:34.400
Why won't you quit those shady jobs?

00:04:35.390 --> 00:04:37.930
Fact is, we're both in too deep now.

00:04:42.570 --> 00:04:45.320
It's a shame we lost Natsumi-san.

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:49.360
She helped us establish this NPO.

00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:52.640
Without her, Shelter wouldn't exist.

00:04:54.400 --> 00:05:00.080
She was happy these kids
had a place they could call home.

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:03.780
We don't trust most adults.

00:05:03.780 --> 00:05:06.400
But we are extremely grateful to Natsumi-san.

00:05:08.570 --> 00:05:12.860
She was a good person, through and through.

00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:20.850
Machi.

00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:25.670
Why do you help the organization?

00:05:33.910 --> 00:05:38.190
I want to help all kids who are in need.

00:05:44.420 --> 00:05:47.190
You're free to laugh.
I know it sounds ridiculous.

00:05:47.190 --> 00:05:49.660
I would never laugh.

00:05:52.710 --> 00:05:54.590
Thanks for dinner.

00:06:10.110 --> 00:06:14.600
That drug dealer was affiliated
with one of our clients.

00:06:15.360 --> 00:06:19.950
You know we received
a cut of their profit, right?

00:06:19.950 --> 00:06:21.780
Yes, Sir.

00:06:21.780 --> 00:06:25.150
We can't go killing our customers.

00:06:25.150 --> 00:06:27.850
I'm holding you accountable, Fuyuhashi.

00:06:27.850 --> 00:06:32.240
Apparently, the brat's girlfriend
was coerced into taking drugs

00:06:32.240 --> 00:06:35.930
so he took it out on the dealer.

00:06:35.930 --> 00:06:39.820
Fuyuhashi couldn't have stopped him.

00:06:39.820 --> 00:06:42.950
I understand how he felt.

00:06:44.200 --> 00:06:46.990
Dealers who prey on children

00:06:46.990 --> 00:06:49.840
aren't worth keeping alive.

00:06:53.530 --> 00:06:56.150
Do you think you're still a child?

00:06:56.150 --> 00:06:58.660
No more acting naive.

00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:00.490
Stand.

00:07:00.490 --> 00:07:02.450
Are you all right?

00:07:04.830 --> 00:07:08.250
Aim higher, Fuyuhashi.

00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:11.380
You know I expect great things from you.

00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:15.390
I'm terribly sorry, Sir.

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:21.080
I'll give our clients an explanation.

00:07:21.080 --> 00:07:25.320
Have the kid turn himself in,
and let Gido-san handle the rest.

00:07:26.410 --> 00:07:28.130
Yes, Sir.

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:42.610
Thanks for putting out this flame.

00:07:42.610 --> 00:07:45.580
I'm truly glad you've adapted to your role.

00:07:45.580 --> 00:07:50.070
No use looking to the past, right?

00:07:52.050 --> 00:07:54.710
You can handle hot beverages now?

00:07:57.640 --> 00:08:00.300
I have them brew it lukewarm.

00:08:01.290 --> 00:08:04.720
Long time no see, Hayase-san.

00:08:06.900 --> 00:08:09.890
Long time no see, Ichika-chan.

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:16.880
What? Want to act as "lovers"
and steal from the organization again?

00:08:19.240 --> 00:08:22.060
Lee-san is here. Shall I call him in?

00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:23.670
Please.

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.290
Thank you for your patience.

00:08:28.290 --> 00:08:29.970
Come on in.

00:08:43.570 --> 00:08:46.760
Bring your business to me, not to Machi.

00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:49.320
Machi's easier to talk to, alright?

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:52.880
Especially since you almost shot me dead.

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:56.160
Machi's not deeply involved in the org.

00:08:56.160 --> 00:08:59.310
Try to keep her out of it.

00:09:08.230 --> 00:09:13.950
So you have yet to find the ten billion yen?

00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:17.970
Yes. We will inform you
when the money is found.

00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:21.520
Please send our regards to Mr. Ma.

00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:35.010
It seems you're keeping up the act.

00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:40.150
The last time we drank alone
was after Gido's death.

00:09:40.150 --> 00:09:43.730
Itching to kill me?

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:52.060
Rest easy. I've got no plans
on disobeying anymore.

00:09:54.430 --> 00:09:56.620
Who was that?

00:09:56.620 --> 00:10:00.830
Mr. Lee, our ambassador from Hong Kong.

00:10:00.830 --> 00:10:04.380
Goroku pays them back 500 million a month.

00:10:04.380 --> 00:10:06.170
So he pays in increments.

00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:10.440
Including interest, he owes them 12 billion
over the next two years.

00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:14.030
That's rough, even for Goroku.

00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:17.820
The organization
is certainly tight on money now.

00:10:17.820 --> 00:10:19.640
Corner him,

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:24.910
and maybe the Hong Kong gang
will deal with Goroku for us.

00:10:26.300 --> 00:10:29.250
How very in character for you, Gido.

00:10:45.570 --> 00:10:47.950
Inspector General Makita?

00:10:50.730 --> 00:10:53.480
Good evening, gentlemen.

00:10:55.230 --> 00:10:57.940
Why is he dining with Goroku?

00:11:05.540 --> 00:11:07.220
Welcome.

00:11:07.220 --> 00:11:10.450
Evening, Yaichi-san. Please, have a seat.

00:11:12.730 --> 00:11:14.940
We thought you wouldn't show.

00:11:14.940 --> 00:11:17.500
What's going on here?

00:11:52.620 --> 00:11:54.580
Baking another cake?

00:11:54.580 --> 00:11:59.910
Yes. I can't ever forget my roots.

00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:03.650
Why not?

00:12:03.650 --> 00:12:06.800
People are creatures of change.

00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:13.260
I saw you at Goroku's place
earlier this evening.

00:12:15.770 --> 00:12:18.840
The man who came after you
was Yaichi Makita.

00:12:18.840 --> 00:12:20.840
He's the leader of the opposing political party

00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:24.180
and your elder brother.

00:12:27.250 --> 00:12:29.360
What's all that about?

00:12:33.950 --> 00:12:38.280
The whale I'm after is none other
than Yaichi Makita himself.

00:12:40.010 --> 00:12:42.690
Goroku hopes to use his illicit wealth

00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:45.470
to make my brother the next prime minister.
[Yaichi Makita]

00:12:45.470 --> 00:12:51.810
Which is why our current
administration backs you.

00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:55.460
Then you plan to arrest your own brother?

00:12:55.460 --> 00:12:57.740
I wish there was another way.

00:12:57.740 --> 00:13:02.540
But if I overlook his crimes,
Goroku's money will control this country.

00:13:02.540 --> 00:13:06.290
Ultimately, justice must prevail.

00:13:06.290 --> 00:13:09.440
How admirable.

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:14.030
But Goroku's currently short on money.

00:13:14.030 --> 00:13:16.250
He's got no business donating to others.

00:13:16.250 --> 00:13:18.080
I made this one less sweet.

00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:20.360
Much obliged.

00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:23.480
Give it a taste.

00:13:23.480 --> 00:13:27.500
So regarding this missing ten billion yen.

00:13:27.500 --> 00:13:31.450
According to the intelligence agency,

00:13:31.450 --> 00:13:35.340
no riches of that amount
have been liquidated yet.

00:13:35.340 --> 00:13:39.190
Then those assets
remain in the country.

00:13:39.190 --> 00:13:43.160
We will find this wealth
and return it to Goroku.

00:13:43.160 --> 00:13:44.300
Return it?

00:13:44.300 --> 00:13:49.680
Goroku will immediately funnel
any money he reclaims to Yaichi.

00:13:51.740 --> 00:13:53.910
And if we prove Ichika stole the riches,

00:13:53.910 --> 00:13:56.350
Goroku won't let her off easy.

00:13:56.350 --> 00:13:57.980
She'd be done for.

00:13:57.980 --> 00:14:03.460
Figure out where this Ichika Kogo
hid the money.

00:14:08.930 --> 00:14:11.420
[Metropolitan Police Department]

00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:18.600
Leave Rikka to us.

00:14:18.600 --> 00:14:22.360
You're always a part of our family, all right?

00:14:22.360 --> 00:14:24.720
Thank you.

00:14:25.680 --> 00:14:28.470
I'm sorry, Rikka.

00:14:41.270 --> 00:14:43.450
I'll be off.

00:14:47.990 --> 00:14:50.600
No, don't go!

00:14:54.650 --> 00:14:56.760
It's a tough sight.

00:14:56.760 --> 00:15:00.780
If only we could do more
than follow Goroku-san's orders.

00:15:05.630 --> 00:15:08.500
[Clearance Law Office]

00:15:24.450 --> 00:15:28.460
That girl's name was Rikka, yes?

00:15:28.460 --> 00:15:30.350
How's she faring?

00:15:34.040 --> 00:15:37.020
Is that all you came to ask?

00:15:42.050 --> 00:15:44.410
I need to ask you for a favor.

00:15:46.080 --> 00:15:49.560
Will you help me get revenge for Natsumi?

00:15:53.950 --> 00:15:56.890
Revenge? Gido's already dead.

00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:59.790
Ichika's the one who killed Natsumi.

00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:03.830
She also stole the missing ten billion.

00:16:04.710 --> 00:16:08.120
I want to figure out
where she's keeping the riches.

00:16:10.440 --> 00:16:13.360
Ichika monitors me through my phone.

00:16:13.360 --> 00:16:16.590
She's got my location at all times.

00:16:16.590 --> 00:16:19.140
I've to be careful around her.

00:16:22.640 --> 00:16:24.380
Machi.

00:16:26.480 --> 00:16:28.960
Won't you help me out?

00:16:28.960 --> 00:16:32.220
I only need you to keep an eye on her.

00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:33.990
Why me?

00:16:33.990 --> 00:16:38.560
You're the only one
in this damn organization I can trust.

00:16:40.680 --> 00:16:43.490
I don't trust you.

00:16:43.490 --> 00:16:45.420
I know.

00:16:46.370 --> 00:16:49.580
But you trusted Natsumi, right?

00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:52.990
Machi-chan!

00:16:52.990 --> 00:16:54.510
Natsumi-san!

00:16:54.510 --> 00:16:56.390
Here, share these with the kids.

00:16:56.390 --> 00:16:57.890
Guys, who wants cake?

00:16:57.890 --> 00:16:59.560
- Cake?
- Me!

00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:03.010
- I want strawberry shortcake.
- Me too!

00:17:03.010 --> 00:17:05.850
Lend me a hand, for her sake.

00:17:06.920 --> 00:17:09.070
Machi, please.

00:17:13.880 --> 00:17:16.390
I'll keep an eye on her, nothing more.

00:17:16.390 --> 00:17:18.450
Then will you help?

00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:23.430
I owe Natsumi-san.

00:17:25.360 --> 00:17:27.520
Thank you.

00:17:27.520 --> 00:17:29.150
I'm using the room.

00:17:29.150 --> 00:17:30.860
Sure.

00:17:30.860 --> 00:17:35.310
First, I'll install a GPS onto her phone.

00:17:35.310 --> 00:17:36.700
[GPinS, Sharing GPS terminal, Input Code]

00:17:38.820 --> 00:17:41.060
There she is!

00:17:43.030 --> 00:17:47.360
I'll also have some people
keep watch over her.

00:17:47.360 --> 00:17:48.430
Yes.

00:17:48.430 --> 00:17:53.550
Everyone's used to this sort of stuff
from their part-time jobs.

00:17:53.550 --> 00:17:57.340
Give us 10 days, and we'll find something.

00:17:58.520 --> 00:18:03.140
That boy's parents never came to visit him
after he turned himself in.

00:18:03.140 --> 00:18:07.340
Apparently, the parents have been reported
for abuse multiple times.

00:18:07.340 --> 00:18:10.070
Sounds like the investigation's going well.

00:18:10.070 --> 00:18:12.000
Gido.

00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:17.810
You found that boy quickly.

00:18:17.810 --> 00:18:22.230
The other divisions
are really starting to suspect you.

00:18:22.230 --> 00:18:25.620
I'm just following my gut, sir.

00:18:25.620 --> 00:18:29.710
You should be glad I'm so capable.

00:18:29.710 --> 00:18:32.200
Treat me to a drink sometime, will you?

00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:37.860
Hey.

00:18:37.860 --> 00:18:39.000
- Good afternoon, Sir.
- Afternoon.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:42.730
I bought us some more Hayase Puddings.

00:18:42.730 --> 00:18:44.190
Again?

00:18:44.190 --> 00:18:48.220
That patisserie's not selling enough.

00:18:48.220 --> 00:18:50.130
I'm just doing what I can do help.

00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:52.150
- Thank you again, Sir.
- Here you go.

00:18:52.150 --> 00:18:54.060
I quite enjoy their pudding.

00:18:54.060 --> 00:18:55.280
- Right?
- Thank you.

00:18:55.280 --> 00:18:58.820
It's a flavor that doesn't get old.

00:18:58.820 --> 00:19:02.350
Too bad the owner's a murderer on the run.

00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:05.340
It's only a matter of time
before they go under.

00:19:05.340 --> 00:19:07.950
His family did no wrong.

00:19:07.950 --> 00:19:09.070
- Thanks for the treat.
- Thank you.

00:19:09.070 --> 00:19:10.780
Sure thing.

00:19:18.620 --> 00:19:24.590
Sir, I have news regarding
the plastic surgeons I looked into.

00:19:24.590 --> 00:19:27.550
An update on Riku Hayase, right? Let's hear it.

00:19:27.550 --> 00:19:30.850
I narrowed down my list of clinics

00:19:30.850 --> 00:19:35.960
to those rumored to take on illicit jobs.

00:19:35.960 --> 00:19:39.130
A client from one of these clinics

00:19:39.130 --> 00:19:42.700
claims to have seen
a man resembling Riku Hayase.

00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:46.080
The clinic in question is a place called
Hitomi Plastic Surgery Clinic.

00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:47.590
[Hitomi Plastic Surgery Clinic]

00:19:50.230 --> 00:19:52.040
I plan to go visit again later.

00:19:52.040 --> 00:19:53.630
I'll join you.

00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:55.650
What?

00:19:55.650 --> 00:19:57.920
It's a new lead.

00:19:57.920 --> 00:20:00.130
We'll give the place a thorough sweep.

00:20:13.110 --> 00:20:15.370
I apologize for the wait.

00:20:15.370 --> 00:20:17.400
One of my operations ran late.

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:18.940
I am Kuwahara, the director.

00:20:18.940 --> 00:20:20.830
Teramoto, from the First Investigation Team.

00:20:20.830 --> 00:20:22.050
Adachi.

00:20:22.050 --> 00:20:24.030
Gido.

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:29.660
The First Investigation Team...

00:20:29.660 --> 00:20:32.790
Then you all deal with serial offenses?

00:20:32.790 --> 00:20:36.170
Yes, you could say that.

00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:40.100
Did something happen to one of my clients?

00:20:41.510 --> 00:20:44.880
- Oh, may I eat?
- Of course. We're the ones bothering.

00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:46.100
This'll only take a moment.

00:20:46.100 --> 00:20:49.360
Much appreciated.

00:20:49.360 --> 00:20:52.750
Do you happen to recognize this individual?

00:20:58.940 --> 00:21:01.660
Can't say I do.

00:21:01.660 --> 00:21:04.530
He wasn't one of your patients?

00:21:04.530 --> 00:21:05.620
No.

00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:09.830
And I never forget my patients.

00:21:09.830 --> 00:21:12.040
So what's all the commotion?

00:21:12.040 --> 00:21:13.880
Is this man a culprit?

00:21:13.880 --> 00:21:19.090
- I'm terribly sorry, but we cannot say any further.
- I see.

00:21:19.090 --> 00:21:20.690
Thank you for your time.

00:21:20.690 --> 00:21:22.200
Let's go.

00:21:23.780 --> 00:21:25.030
Excuse us.

00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:28.080
Say, could I see your ear?

00:21:28.080 --> 00:21:32.200
- My ear?
- I was admiring its beauty.

00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:35.930
I'll catch up.

00:21:40.420 --> 00:21:42.980
What an ideal shape.

00:21:42.980 --> 00:21:44.880
Thank you.

00:21:44.880 --> 00:21:48.060
Come in for a follow-up when you can.

00:21:54.940 --> 00:21:56.370
What's your read on her?

00:21:56.370 --> 00:21:58.580
She seemed a bit too calm.

00:21:58.580 --> 00:22:01.310
That might just be what she's like, though.

00:22:01.310 --> 00:22:03.610
May I look into this a bit further?

00:22:03.610 --> 00:22:05.940
I promise it won't affect my other jobs.

00:22:05.940 --> 00:22:07.810
You're really stuck on this place.

00:22:07.810 --> 00:22:09.940
It's called a detective's hunch.

00:22:09.940 --> 00:22:11.260
Right, Mr. Gido?

00:22:11.260 --> 00:22:12.940
Fine, do what you want.

00:22:12.940 --> 00:22:15.080
Much appreciated, Sir.

00:22:18.930 --> 00:22:23.100
It's only a matter of time
until my reboot is uncovered.

00:22:27.130 --> 00:22:29.480
Here you go.

00:22:33.170 --> 00:22:35.220
Thank you.

00:22:43.650 --> 00:22:46.000
What a nostalgic flavor.

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:47.790
Nostalgic?

00:22:49.410 --> 00:22:54.970
Natsumi-san used to bring your cakes to Shelter.

00:22:55.630 --> 00:22:57.950
I see.

00:23:00.210 --> 00:23:05.130
Street kids like us
didn't grow up eating cake.

00:23:05.130 --> 00:23:08.940
So this taste is cemented in our hearts.

00:23:17.420 --> 00:23:20.540
Guess I'll bring some the next time I visit.

00:23:20.540 --> 00:23:25.020
I need people to help me eat my stash.

00:23:25.810 --> 00:23:28.270
Would Fuyuhashi get mad at me if I did?

00:23:28.270 --> 00:23:30.190
He wouldn't.

00:23:30.190 --> 00:23:36.250
He wants the kiddos to eat good food.

00:23:36.250 --> 00:23:37.900
Is that so?

00:23:37.900 --> 00:23:40.180
Then I'll bring you all plenty.

00:23:49.840 --> 00:23:51.600
You look better like that.

00:23:51.600 --> 00:23:53.420
What?

00:23:53.420 --> 00:23:55.470
With a smile on your face.

00:23:56.620 --> 00:23:59.920
It makes you look kinder.

00:24:07.790 --> 00:24:10.450
Have some Cheesecake and Mont Blanc, too.

00:24:10.450 --> 00:24:11.980
I only came to make my report.

00:24:11.980 --> 00:24:15.780
No, I insist. These came out delicious.

00:24:15.780 --> 00:24:18.420
You should definitely give them a try.

00:24:18.420 --> 00:24:20.080
Then I'll just take a Cheesecake.

00:24:20.080 --> 00:24:24.050
Don't hold back. Take the Mont Blanc!

00:24:35.350 --> 00:24:37.610
Here's Ichika's general routine.

00:24:37.610 --> 00:24:42.960
First, she stops by the hospital
to eat breakfast with her sister.

00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:44.900
From there, she heads off to work.

00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:48.610
She never met up with anyone
aside from her work clients.

00:24:50.770 --> 00:24:55.000
These are her exact routes
according to the GPS.

00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:58.430
Aside from her home,
the hospital, and her office,

00:24:58.430 --> 00:25:01.430
she visited three places.

00:25:01.430 --> 00:25:04.150
The first place was a plastic surgeon.
[Hitomi Plastic Surgery Clinic]

00:25:04.150 --> 00:25:07.340
She must've given the doctor hush money.

00:25:07.340 --> 00:25:10.110
The second place is here.

00:25:10.110 --> 00:25:12.520
An abandoned building in Tama City.
[Wholesale Market]

00:25:12.520 --> 00:25:14.850
Bingo.

00:25:14.850 --> 00:25:18.270
That's where she's keeping the money.

00:25:19.160 --> 00:25:20.650
I'll go check it out.

00:25:20.650 --> 00:25:23.300
No, don't. It's too dangerous.

00:25:23.300 --> 00:25:25.320
I'll handle the rest from here.

00:25:25.320 --> 00:25:28.090
Call me when Ichika's headed there.

00:25:28.090 --> 00:25:30.360
I'll catch her red-handed.

00:25:31.950 --> 00:25:33.700
Okay.

00:25:34.380 --> 00:25:39.010
There's one more place she was visiting.

00:25:56.000 --> 00:25:58.460
So you didn't know.

00:25:59.090 --> 00:26:01.570
She helps out there from time to time.

00:26:05.930 --> 00:26:08.170
I'll be heading out shortly.

00:26:08.170 --> 00:26:11.140
Once this cools, you can decorate them.

00:26:11.140 --> 00:26:12.590
Thank you, Ichika-san.

00:26:12.590 --> 00:26:14.470
Of course.

00:26:15.770 --> 00:26:18.610
Don't be late to school, Takumi-kun.

00:26:18.610 --> 00:26:20.180
I won't.

00:26:20.180 --> 00:26:22.230
I'm almost done.

00:26:22.230 --> 00:26:25.080
His concentration is admirable.

00:26:25.080 --> 00:26:27.520
He really is a Hayase.

00:26:27.520 --> 00:26:29.050
We all love our pastries here.

00:26:29.050 --> 00:26:31.950
He's just like my son.

00:26:31.950 --> 00:26:38.150
[Hayase Patisserie]

00:26:47.100 --> 00:26:49.490
What're you playing at?

00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:51.290
I'm only helping out.

00:26:51.290 --> 00:26:57.100
I wouldn't mind replicating other desserts
if you gave me your recipes.

00:26:57.100 --> 00:26:59.650
Enough with the blackmail.

00:26:59.650 --> 00:27:02.650
I said I had no plans
on disobeying, didn't I?

00:27:16.620 --> 00:27:18.580
[Inspector General Makita]

00:27:20.440 --> 00:27:23.450
- Hello?
- The Second Investigation Team is on the move.

00:27:23.450 --> 00:27:26.860
They're headed to the Clearance Law Office.

00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:31.010
They got word
of Fuyuhashi's group using the place.

00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:34.550
Do what you will with this intel.

00:27:43.030 --> 00:27:44.850
Hello?

00:27:44.850 --> 00:27:46.380
Where are you right now?

00:27:46.380 --> 00:27:47.820
At the office. Why?

00:27:47.820 --> 00:27:51.070
Run. The police are coming.

00:27:52.310 --> 00:27:53.970
Guys. Leave, now.

00:27:53.970 --> 00:27:55.160
The police are coming.

00:27:55.160 --> 00:27:57.180
- The police?
- Hurry!

00:27:57.180 --> 00:28:00.970
- Take the elevator!
- What?

00:28:04.470 --> 00:28:07.970
- Police!
- Run!

00:28:13.080 --> 00:28:14.540
Police. Stop right there!

00:28:14.540 --> 00:28:18.030
Stop!

00:28:19.850 --> 00:28:22.300
Stop right there!

00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:25.740
No, stop!

00:28:31.890 --> 00:28:33.340
- Call an ambulance!
- Yes, Ma'am!

00:28:33.340 --> 00:28:34.990
Hurry!

00:28:39.430 --> 00:28:41.640
Rikka?

00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:43.630
Rikka!

00:28:45.580 --> 00:28:48.170
Rikka!

00:29:11.140 --> 00:29:15.580
Don't worry. I've deleted our call history.

00:29:22.300 --> 00:29:24.160
How is Rikka?

00:29:26.680 --> 00:29:29.850
She passed on the way to the hospital.

00:29:41.070 --> 00:29:43.130
When I first met her...

00:29:44.830 --> 00:29:48.140
She said she couldn't do what others could.

00:29:50.770 --> 00:29:55.420
She said she had nowhere to go.

00:29:58.150 --> 00:30:00.930
That's why I introduced her to this job.

00:30:03.780 --> 00:30:06.200
Her death isn't your fault.

00:30:07.740 --> 00:30:09.700
I know.

00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:20.470
I wouldn't survive if I kept blaming myself.

00:30:22.240 --> 00:30:23.970
I just...

00:30:27.350 --> 00:30:30.210
I can't believe how little I can do.

00:30:34.580 --> 00:30:37.080
If I had the status...

00:30:39.580 --> 00:30:41.970
If I had the money...

00:30:44.610 --> 00:30:46.760
I could have saved her.

00:31:06.220 --> 00:31:14.800
♪ Remember the good things,
remember the good ♪

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:20.370
Your hero has arrived, Machi-chan!

00:31:22.820 --> 00:31:25.550
You sure it's fine, meeting Machi and all?

00:31:25.550 --> 00:31:29.980
The officers already know
I have ties to Fuyuhashi.

00:31:29.980 --> 00:31:32.600
You're walking a fine line there.

00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:34.120
Eventually, you'll take a tumble.

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.470
And I'm surprised to see you kicking.

00:31:36.470 --> 00:31:39.630
I'm down a finger though, no thanks to you.

00:31:41.800 --> 00:31:44.500
They were about to snuff me out.

00:31:44.500 --> 00:31:47.850
I got away with my life
because they found Gido.

00:31:49.710 --> 00:31:52.600
Except, what do I find
when I leave the hospital?

00:31:52.600 --> 00:31:57.850
A brand new Gido-san to take the old one's place!

00:31:59.390 --> 00:32:03.180
My condolences to you, good sir.

00:32:03.180 --> 00:32:08.670
But that doesn't mean I forgive you
for setting me up.

00:32:09.660 --> 00:32:14.710
I'll eagerly watch as you self-implode.

00:32:19.760 --> 00:32:24.430
Machi-chan! I've come for you!

00:32:25.500 --> 00:32:27.050
Get on in.

00:32:45.250 --> 00:32:48.470
I had them release Machi-chan for now.

00:32:48.470 --> 00:32:50.620
Though she's still a suspect,

00:32:50.620 --> 00:32:55.050
I've set it up so the ringleader was...

00:32:55.050 --> 00:32:58.150
What was her name again?
The green, dead girl.

00:32:58.150 --> 00:32:59.460
Rikka.

00:32:59.460 --> 00:33:04.800
Right. Rikka will be
our sacrificial ringleader.

00:33:06.020 --> 00:33:08.810
That office solely existed
to keep tabs on part-timers.

00:33:08.810 --> 00:33:12.280
There was no evidence
hinting at our monetary schemes there.

00:33:12.280 --> 00:33:16.780
Machi-chan also transferred
all confidential data elsewhere.

00:33:16.780 --> 00:33:21.310
The police didn't find any ties
to the organization as well.

00:33:21.310 --> 00:33:24.010
And though I'll get ratted out
since the office is in my name,

00:33:24.010 --> 00:33:28.390
it won't be anything fatal.

00:33:28.390 --> 00:33:30.620
Thank you.

00:33:31.480 --> 00:33:36.760
It's truly an honor
to have you back, Kaieda-san.

00:33:38.910 --> 00:33:43.570
I'll prove myself useful to you, Goroku-san.

00:33:43.570 --> 00:33:46.550
I'll return the money I stole as well.

00:33:48.520 --> 00:33:51.060
It was a close call,

00:33:51.060 --> 00:33:54.680
but I'm glad we got off scot-free.

00:33:56.570 --> 00:33:58.200
Scot-free?

00:33:59.250 --> 00:34:00.560
Rikka died.

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:01.650
Machi.

00:34:01.650 --> 00:34:06.730
You must be the one
who wrangles the youngsters

00:34:06.730 --> 00:34:09.250
under Fuyuhashi.

00:34:09.250 --> 00:34:14.220
Our organization could use
young talent like you.

00:34:14.220 --> 00:34:15.710
Please, have a seat.

00:34:23.160 --> 00:34:28.370
I'd like to have you handle work
for our organization.

00:34:28.370 --> 00:34:31.050
Any objections to that, folks?

00:34:31.050 --> 00:34:34.830
Not at all.

00:34:37.870 --> 00:34:39.860
Goroku-san.

00:34:40.570 --> 00:34:43.000
Machi represents our NPO.

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:46.110
Her involvement could affect Shelter.

00:34:46.110 --> 00:34:48.430
That hideout for homeless kids?

00:34:48.430 --> 00:34:50.450
It's still up and running?

00:34:50.450 --> 00:34:53.550
We'll have someone else handle the NPO.

00:34:53.550 --> 00:34:56.520
Machi-san will join our ranks.

00:34:56.520 --> 00:34:57.990
Understood?

00:35:01.400 --> 00:35:02.880
Now then.

00:35:06.970 --> 00:35:11.290
Here's to our newest member.

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:15.280
Cheers.

00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:17.680
Cheers.

00:35:27.940 --> 00:35:30.160
I thought I'd have a heart attack.

00:35:30.160 --> 00:35:34.390
They called me a "member." Hilarious!

00:35:34.390 --> 00:35:37.990
Maybe now we can actually expand Shelter.

00:35:39.180 --> 00:35:42.310
Machi, you sure you're okay?

00:35:42.310 --> 00:35:44.240
Don't push yourself.

00:35:46.320 --> 00:35:49.020
Says you.

00:35:50.410 --> 00:35:53.180
You do all the dirty work for our sakes.

00:35:53.180 --> 00:35:56.320
You're the one pushing yourself.

00:35:56.320 --> 00:35:59.420
I'm more worried about you.

00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:05.570
Aren't you reaching your limits?

00:36:08.370 --> 00:36:12.380
Let's become powerful enough
to make do on our own.

00:36:18.750 --> 00:36:21.660
Don't ever say that again.

00:36:59.480 --> 00:37:03.810
Want to join me in bringing Goroku down?

00:37:09.110 --> 00:37:12.930
If you inherit his role,
you'll finally be free.

00:37:19.060 --> 00:37:22.070
Ichika's the one who murdered Natsumi.

00:37:22.070 --> 00:37:25.170
She's also the one who stole the ten billion.

00:37:26.610 --> 00:37:30.740
- How can you be so sure?
- Ichika told me herself.

00:37:30.740 --> 00:37:35.040
She wants to use me to usurp Goroku.

00:37:38.510 --> 00:37:42.080
But I know where she's keeping the money.

00:37:44.050 --> 00:37:46.100
Make that known,

00:37:46.100 --> 00:37:51.140
and the Hong Kong gang
will hold Goroku responsible.

00:37:51.140 --> 00:37:54.170
Once they've killed him,
the organization's yours.

00:37:57.800 --> 00:38:00.290
What's in it for you?

00:38:00.290 --> 00:38:03.260
I get to put an end to Ichika.

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:13.180
But when you take over,
I want you to let me and my family go.

00:38:13.180 --> 00:38:16.320
Promise me that, and I'll make sure
the police won't get you.

00:38:16.320 --> 00:38:19.550
I know a guy who can make that happen.

00:38:22.680 --> 00:38:26.000
I can't trust a word you say.

00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:30.990
If Ichika-san's the mastermind,
then she's likely marking you.

00:38:30.990 --> 00:38:34.570
She bugged my phone.

00:38:34.570 --> 00:38:39.810
Then how on earth did you find the money?

00:38:40.800 --> 00:38:43.670
Machi helped.

00:38:43.670 --> 00:38:47.020
Said she'd help for Natsumi's sake.

00:38:56.510 --> 00:38:59.040
The number you have called is...

00:39:00.160 --> 00:39:02.200
Where's the ten billion?

00:39:02.200 --> 00:39:03.380
What?

00:39:03.380 --> 00:39:07.340
She's going to steal it for our family.

00:39:07.340 --> 00:39:09.560
Where's the money?

00:39:29.640 --> 00:39:35.640
♫ It's wise not to expect anything ♫

00:39:35.640 --> 00:39:40.370
Hey, could I help?

00:39:40.370 --> 00:39:43.010
Sure, that'd seriously help us out!

00:39:43.010 --> 00:39:45.960
Could you pass out the chopsticks and plates?

00:39:45.960 --> 00:39:48.350
- Sure!
- Thanks.

00:39:50.090 --> 00:39:53.050
♫ Whatever you do ♫

00:39:53.050 --> 00:39:55.660
There.
[Shelter]

00:39:55.660 --> 00:39:59.150
Yes, looks good.

00:39:59.150 --> 00:40:02.710
From here on out, we're all a family.

00:40:02.710 --> 00:40:04.880
No kid will go homeless on our watch.

00:40:04.880 --> 00:40:09.060
- Our family will only continue to grow.
- Yes.

00:40:09.060 --> 00:40:13.950
♫ It just becomes empty little by little ♫

00:40:13.950 --> 00:40:15.850
♫ My heart just becomes empty ♫

00:40:15.850 --> 00:40:20.910
♫ My heart just becomes empty ♫

00:40:22.250 --> 00:40:27.990
♫ "Are you laughing more than usual?" ♫

00:40:27.990 --> 00:40:29.010
Machi...

00:40:29.010 --> 00:40:33.080
♫ Did such a day even exist? ♫

00:40:33.080 --> 00:40:35.960
♫ Did such a day even exist? ♫

00:40:35.960 --> 00:40:39.040
Fuyuhashi, wait!

00:40:39.040 --> 00:40:42.750
♫ The treasure that shines in my heart ♫

00:40:42.750 --> 00:40:44.480
Fuyuhashi!

00:41:00.420 --> 00:41:01.970
Machi!

00:41:01.970 --> 00:41:03.620
Fuyuhashi!

00:41:06.490 --> 00:41:09.980
Machi, are you all right? Machi!

00:41:09.980 --> 00:41:12.170
I'm sorry.

00:41:13.780 --> 00:41:17.130
I couldn't make our dream come true.

00:41:20.030 --> 00:41:22.350
Fuyuhashi.

00:41:25.480 --> 00:41:29.760
Thanks for becoming my family.

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:38.680
Machi.

00:41:38.680 --> 00:41:40.100
Machi!

00:41:40.100 --> 00:41:43.400
Wake up! Machi!

00:41:43.400 --> 00:41:45.240
Machi...

00:41:46.320 --> 00:41:48.010
Machi?

00:41:48.010 --> 00:41:50.230
Machi!

00:41:50.230 --> 00:41:52.270
Machi!

00:42:00.240 --> 00:42:03.020
Machi!

00:42:03.020 --> 00:42:05.010
Machi...

00:42:08.600 --> 00:42:10.570
Someone's here.

00:42:14.360 --> 00:42:15.830
Go.

00:42:25.340 --> 00:42:27.810
Come on.

00:42:27.810 --> 00:42:29.710
Hold it.

00:42:30.890 --> 00:42:33.060
Cut it.

00:42:36.460 --> 00:42:38.920
Go in.

00:42:40.250 --> 00:42:42.220
So?

00:42:45.210 --> 00:42:49.320
You need to report these things, Gido.

00:42:49.320 --> 00:42:51.400
How did you find us?

00:42:52.300 --> 00:42:54.880
It was me.

00:43:01.950 --> 00:43:04.300
Goroku-san told me to report

00:43:04.300 --> 00:43:10.290
if Fuyuhashi-san ever acted suspicious...

00:43:19.840 --> 00:43:22.470
Ichika's the one who stole the money.

00:43:25.550 --> 00:43:29.480
She had my family held as hostages.

00:43:30.650 --> 00:43:33.060
That's why I didn't...

00:43:33.060 --> 00:43:35.370
Kiriya. Their call history.

00:43:35.370 --> 00:43:37.320
Right.

00:43:52.070 --> 00:43:54.450
Ichika-san's the last person they called.
[I]

00:44:10.600 --> 00:44:15.690
I have plenty to say to you two,
but first things first.

00:44:15.690 --> 00:44:18.140
Go catch Ichika.

00:44:27.510 --> 00:44:31.250
Can I kill her?

00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:35.290
Now that's a good look.

00:44:50.250 --> 00:44:52.260
Fuyuhashi.

00:44:53.410 --> 00:44:55.590
I'm sorry.

00:44:55.590 --> 00:44:59.650
Machi doesn't blame you.

00:44:59.650 --> 00:45:02.240
She made this choice herself.

00:45:03.480 --> 00:45:06.540
She chose to come here, for her family.

00:45:27.790 --> 00:45:30.640
I'm so sorry, Machi-chan.

00:45:32.730 --> 00:45:42.730
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:45:42.730 --> 00:45:46.880
[Reboot]

00:45:46.880 --> 00:45:48.480
I've had enough.
[Next, Episode 8: Truth]

00:45:48.480 --> 00:45:49.650
Fuyuhashi's getting in the way.

00:45:49.650 --> 00:45:52.300
Tell me. Who murdered Natsumi?

00:45:52.300 --> 00:45:53.860
Enough!

00:45:53.860 --> 00:45:55.610
No matter what happens, live.

00:45:55.610 --> 00:45:58.090
Dad's coming home, right?
[The truth behind Natsumi's death is finally revealed]

00:45:58.090 --> 00:45:59.600
We can finally avenge your wife.
[In her final moments, Ichika visited "that place"]

00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:02.910
Stop, please!
[A cruel reality unfolds...]

00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:07.380
I'll die as the culprit
who stole the ten billion yen.

00:46:07.380 --> 00:46:13.990
♫ Softly, softly, it shone gently again today ♫

00:46:13.990 --> 00:46:17.400
[Shelter]